{"questionId":"816fedc1-1434-4eb8-aa3b-6715a1e738ae_22","correctAnswer":"-196","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Find vertex x from midpoint of zeros","content":"Zeros: $2x-20=0 \\Rightarrow x=10$; $2x+8=0 \\Rightarrow x=-4$. Vertex $x = \\frac{10+(-4)}{2} = 3$."},{"title":"Evaluate f(3) to get minimum","content":"$f(3)=(2(3)-20)(2(3)+8)=(-14)(14)=-196$. That matches choice &minus;196 &mdash; <strong>&minus;196</strong> is correct.","desmosExpressions":["y=(2x-20)(2x+8)","(3,-196)"]}]}